04/02/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Outgoing Prime Minister Hashim Thaci and head of the European Commission Liaison Office in Kosovo Renzo Daviddi signed an agreement Thursday (February 3rd) that gives Kosovo 63.9m euros.
These funds were pledged by the EU at a donors' conference and are part of the Instrument for Pre-Accession Assistance Programme.
Thaci said the funds demonstrate the EU's commitment to Kosovo's development.
Daviddi said that they are aimed at boosting the everyday quality of life and to help Kosovo move closer to EU standards.
(Koha Ditore - 04/02/11;
RTK, Kohavision, Klan Kosova - 03/02/11)
